The paper discusses the use of neural networks for machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves training deep neural networks, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image processing, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the use of hyperparameters to optimize the neural network, which is a common technique in deep learning (cs.DL).
